#. Tag: title
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Assistive Technologies"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &gnome; desktop includes assistive technologies to support users with various impairments and special needs, and to interact with common assistive devices. This chapter describes several assistive technology applications designed to meet the needs of users with physical disabilities like low vision or impaired motor skills."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:25
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling Assistive Technologies"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "To configure accessibility features, open the respective settings dialog by right-clicking the desktop and choosing <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> and then <guimenu>Universal Access</guimenu> . Each assistive feature can be enabled separately using this dialog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:34
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you need a more direct access to individual assistive features, turn on <guimenu>Always Show Universal Access Menu</guimenu> in the <guimenu>Universal Access</guimenu> dialog. A new menu will appear on the bottom panel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "Visual Assistance"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the <guimenu>Seeing</guimenu> section of the <guimenu>Universal Access</guimenu> dialog, you can enable features that help people with impaired vision."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "Turning on <guimenu>High Contrast</guimenu> enables high contrast black and white icons in the &gnome; desktop."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Turning on <guimenu>Large Text</guimenu> enlarges the font used in the user interface."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Turning on <guimenu>Zoom</guimenu> enables a screen magnifier. You can set the desired magnification and magnifier behavior, including color effects."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "By customizing the <guimenu>Cursor Size</guimenu> you can increase the visibility of the mousecursor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the <guimenu>Screen Reader</guimenu> is turned on, any UI element or text that receives keyboard focus is read aloud."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the <guimenu>Sound Keys</guimenu> are turned on, a sound is played whenever <keycap>Num Lock</keycap> or <keycap>Caps Lock</keycap> are turned on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hearing Assistance"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the <guimenu>Hearing</guimenu> section of the <guimenu>Universal Access</guimenu> dialog, you can enable features helping people with impaired hearing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:99
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the <guimenu>Visual Alerts</guimenu> are turned on, a window title or the entire screen is flashed when an alert sound occurs for the respective application."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keyboard and Mouse"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the <guimenu>Typing</guimenu> and <guimenu>Pointing and Clicking</guimenu> sections of the <guimenu>Universal Access</guimenu> dialog, you can enable features that help people with mobility impairments."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the <guimenu>Screen Keyboard</guimenu> is turned on, a virtual keyboard appears whenever you need to enter text. You can use the screen keyboard by clicking the virtual keys."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:123
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Repeat Keys</guimenu> lets you configure if and when a key is repeated when it is pressed for a longer time. You can either turn this feature <guimenu>Off</guimenu> or configure a <guimenu>Delay</guimenu> and the <guimenu>Speed</guimenu> by which keys are repeated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Under <guimenu>Cursor Blinking</guimenu> you can configure if and at which speed the cursor blinks in text fileds (for example in a terminal)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Typing Assist (AccessX)</guimenu> to open a dialog where you can enable various features that make typing easier:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:143
#, no-c-format
msgid "With <guimenu>Enable by Keyboard</guimenu> , you can turn accessibility features on or off by using the keyboard."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Sticky Keys</guimenu> allows you to type key combinations one key at a time rather than having to hold down all of the keys at once. For example, the <keycombo> <keycap function=\"alt\"/><keycap function=\"tab\"/></keycombo> shortcut switches between windows."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:156
#, no-c-format
msgid "With sticky keys turned off, you need to hold down both keys at the same time. With sticky keys turned on, press <keycap function=\"alt\"/> and then <keycap function=\"tab\"/> to do the same."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:163
#, no-c-format
msgid "Turn on <guimenu>Slow Keys</guimenu> if you want a delay between pressing a key and the letter being displayed on the screen. This means that you need to hold down each key you want to type for a little while before it appears. Use slow keys if you accidentally press several keys at a time when you type, or if you find it difficult to press the right key on the keyboard first time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "Turn on <guimenu>Bounce Keys</guimenu> to ignore key presses that are rapidly repeated. This can help, for example, if you have hand tremors which cause you to press a key multiple times when you only want to press it once."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:183
#, no-c-format
msgid "Turn on <guimenu>Mouse Keys</guimenu> to control the mouse pointer using the numeric keypad on your keyboard."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:189
#, no-c-format
msgid "Click <guimenu>Click Assist</guimenu> to open a dialog where you can enable various features that make clicking easier: simulated secondary click and hover click."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "Turn on <guimenu>Simulated Secondary Click</guimenu> to activate the secondary click (usually the right mouse button) by holding down the primary button for a predefined <guimenu>Acceptance delay</guimenu> . This is useful if you find it difficult to move your fingers individually on one hand, or if your pointing device only has a single button."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:206
#, no-c-format
msgid "Turn on <guimenu>Hover Click</guimenu> to trigger a click by hovering your mouse pointer over an object on the screen. This is useful if you find it difficult to move the mouse and click at the same time. If this feature is turned on, a small Hover Click window opens and stays above all of your other windows. You can use this to choose what sort of click should happen when you hover. When you hover your mouse pointer over a button and do not move it, the pointer gradually changes color. When it has fully changed color, the button will be clicked."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use the slider to adjust the <guimenu>Double-Click Delay</guimenu> according to your needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "For More Information"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: gnome_accessibility.xml:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can find further information in the &gnome; help, which is also available online at <link xlink:href=\"https://help.gnome.org/users/gnome-help/3.26/a11y.html.en\"/> ."
msgstr ""

